Tanzania is planning at least $650
million in projects to bring more potable water to Dar es Salaam
and rural areas, Minister for Water Jumanne Maghembe said.  With Tanzania among the fastest-growing economies in
Africa, the government wants to concentrate on irrigation to
expand the  agriculture sector  and water infrastructure projects
